Implemented and committed T-037.

Commit: `4f0e672 feat(render): add deterministic replay harness [T-037@20260416T181925Z]`

What changed:
- Added [replay.py](/Users/anthony/Programming/PromptClaw/my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/replay.py): `replay(score, seeds, delta_track)` returns a `PerformedPart`, matching deltas by `event_id` or sequence index and replaying performance-level fields while preserving score-level fields.
- Extended export/sidecar flow in [audio_sidecar.py](/Users/anthony/Programming/PromptClaw/my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/audio_sidecar.py) and [export.py](/Users/anthony/Programming/PromptClaw/my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/export.py) so supplied delta tracks are persisted as `.delta.json` alongside audio and referenced by the metadata sidecar.
- Added [test_render_replay.py](/Users/anthony/Programming/PromptClaw/tests/test_render_replay.py) verifying event-sequence hash identity across replay, including timing, velocity, and articulation values, plus replay from persisted delta JSON.

